Recipe number: Steak hache with pommes frites and cheats Bearnaise sauce

Ingredient: 2 skinless chicken breast fillets (or use turkey breast)
1tbsp crunchy peanut butter (choose a sugar-free version with no palm oil, if possible)
sunflower oil, for wiping the pan
2 Little Gem lettuce hearts, cut into wedges
1 banana shallot, halved and thinly sliced
1 large red onion, halved and thinly sliced
4 tbsp tagine spice paste or 2 tbsp harissa
190ml bottle pomegranate juice (not sweetened; we used Pom Wonderful)
600g carrots, washed and coarsely grated (no need to peel)
1l hot vegetable stock (from a cube is fine)
125ml milk (to make it dairy-free, see 'try' below)
plain yogurt and naan bread, to serve

Recipe number: Prawn & salmon burgers with spicy mayo
Ingredient: 180g pack peeled raw prawns , roughly chopped
4 skinless salmon fillets, chopped into small chunks
4 seeded burger buns , toasted, to serve
400g can borlotti or fava beans , juice reserved
2 Little Gem lettuces cut into wedges
sprinkling of dried chilli flakes and roughly chopped flat-leaf parsley, optional
4 vegan sausages (we used Dee’s leek & onion)
1 large kale leaf stem removed, washed
